1.title: The "Pop" in Pop Culture

episode of.title: The A.V. Club Hosted By John Teti (TV Series 2017– )

1.plot: The A.V. Club, the taste-making entertainment website, had made the jump to TV with a new comedy and commentary show on Fusion. Each week, host John Teti will dive into another corner of pop culture, from The Oscars to Oscar The Grouch. With special Guest Bob Odenkirk.

20.title: The Price Is Right

episode of.title: The A.V. Club Hosted By John Teti (TV Series 2017– )

20.plot: On the next episode of The A.V. Club we leave our Chicago home-base to discover all there is to know about The Price Is Right. Join us as we discover all the aspects of what makes this long running show so special.

imdb.plot outline: "The A.V. Club" Hosted By John Teti, air Thursdays at 9pm on Fusion TV. The irreverent, Chicago-based series features the editorial brains behind the taste-making entertainment website, AVClub.com, sharing their distinct perspective on movies, music, television, and more. Recent topics have included a fall TV preview, food trends, The Price is Right, cord cutting and the viewing habits of TV watchers, roles for women in Hollywood, entertainment awards, Twitter, the polarizing effects of the series "Girls," the 'Black TV' renaissance and more. Each week, Teti dives into another corner of pop culture, covering everything from The Oscars to Oscar the Grouch. The series is produced by Onion Studios, with Alicia Haywood, MaryBeth Searls and James Fleischel serving as executive producers. This marks the first series from one of Fusion Media Group's digital brands to premiere on FUSION TV.
